WHAT IS THIS FILE
The certified computing profile for the Intel Core Ultra 9 285H mobile
processor, based on the Arrow Lake architecture. It defines the hybrid
CPU cluster (Lion Cove P-cores + Skymont E-cores), Intel Arc GPU (8 Xe
cores), AI Boost NPU (13 TOPS INT8), and the LPDDR5x memory controller.
Every subsystem is expressed through auditable formulas.

WHY IT EXISTS
Arrow Lake introduces a disaggregated tile design with Foveros 3D
packaging, combining TSMC N3B (CPU), N5/N6 (GPU/IO), and Intel 22FFL
(base tile) processes. GIOP models this as formulas so that AI-
accelerated grading, rendering, and video encoding/decoding times are
predictable on Intel-powered mobile workstations.

HOW IT WORKS
CPU Core Cluster:
  P-cores (Lion Cove): 6 cores, up to 5.4 GHz, Hyper-Threading disabled
    by design. 3 MB L2 per core, shared 24 MB L3.
  E-cores (Skymont): 8 cores, up to 4.5 GHz. 4 MB L2 per cluster (4 cores).
  LP-E cores: 2 Skymont at up to 2.5 GHz for background tasks.
  IPC uplift: Lion Cove ≈ 1.13× Raptor Cove (Geekbench 6 single-thread).

CPU Multi-Core Throughput (Amdahl):
  P(N) = 1 / ((1 - f_parallel) + f_parallel / N)
  where f_parallel = 0.90, N = 14 (6P + 8E). Measured multi-core
  Geekbench 6 ≈ 14,200.

CPU Dynamic Power:
  P_cpu = C_eff * V^2 * f
  P-core: C_eff ≈ 1.8 nF (N3B), V = 0.65–1.10 V, f_max = 5.4 GHz.
  E-core: C_eff ≈ 0.6 nF, V = 0.60–1.00 V, f_max = 4.5 GHz.
  Total base power: 45 W TDP, configurable up to 115 W turbo.

NPU AI Boost (13 TOPS INT8):
  TOPS_INT8 = (MAC_units * 2 * f_npu) / 1e12
  ≈ (3,072 * 2 * 2.1e9) / 1e12 ≈ 12.9 TOPS (marketed 13 TOPS).
  Combined platform TOPS (CPU + GPU + NPU) up to 99.

GPU Compute (Intel Arc, 8 Xe cores):
  FP16 TFLOPS:
    TFLOPS_FP16 = (Xe_cores * EUs_per_Xe * 2 * 2 * f_gpu) / 1e12
    = (8 * 16 * 2 * 2 * 2.35e9) / 1e12 ≈ 9.6 TFLOPS
  FP32 TFLOPS:
    TFLOPS_FP32 = TFLOPS_FP16 / 2 ≈ 4.8 TFLOPS
  Supports DirectML, OpenVINO, ONNX RT, WebNN for AI inference.

Memory Subsystem (LPDDR5x-8400, 128-bit):
  Bus width: 128 bits = 16 bytes.
  Data rate: 8.4 Gbps per pin.
  Bandwidth:
    BW = bus_width_bytes * f_data * 2(DDR)
    = 16 * 8.4e9 * 2 = 268.8 GB/s
  Max capacity: 64 GB LPDDR5x.

Media Engine (Hardware Codec):
  H.266/VVC 8K 60 fps decode, AV1 8K 60 fps encode/decode.
  Encoding throughput (AV1, 8K, 4:2:0 10-bit):
    R_encode = f_media * pixels_per_cycle
    ≈ 1.2e9 * 4 ≈ 4.8 Gpix/s (sufficient for 8K 60 fps).
  Transcoding latency (single 8K frame): ~12 ms.

WHERE IT IS DEPLOYED
- Dell XPS 17, Lenovo ThinkPad X1 Extreme, HP ZBook Fury G12.
- GIOP mobile grading workstations, on-set DIT carts, AI-assisted
  denoising and encoding.

